Sin City of the South. Gambling halls and brothels flourished on Monmouth 
Street, the main strip. But in 1982, a newly elected city commission banned 
nude dancing and then began strict enforcement of liquor and vice laws. 
American Album visits a town working to clean up -- and to construct a legal 
economy. The Kentucky Post 
</P>
