<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHOT KILLS WOMAN IN OCEAN BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman was shot and killed in an Ocean Beach apartment late Sunday morning, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police, responding to a call about at an apartment complex in the 4900 block of 
Muir Avenue about 11 a.m., found the woman with a gunshot in the upper body. 
Emergency crews summoned to the apartment were unable to resuscitate the woman, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Homicide investigators were interviewing two people who were reportedly inside 
the apartment when the shooting occurred. Police also recovered a 
semi-automatic pistol. The victim's name was being withheld because relatives 
had not been notified, police said. 
</P>
