<HEADLINE>
<P>
VANEMBRICQS PACES UCLA WOMEN, 68-57 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Senior forward Sandra VanEmbricqs scored 14 points, grabbed nine rebounds and 
had four steals to lead the UCLA women's basketball team to a 68-57 win over 
West Virginia Sunday at Pauley Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
The Bruins (2-0) ran off to an early 10-0 lead and increased the advantage to 
16 points at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
West Virginia (0-1) rallied in the second half, behind the 14-point scoring of 
sophomore center Tracy Slogik to cut its deficit to 61-57, before the Bruins 
scored the next eight points for the win. 
</P>
<P>
Senior forward Michele Wootton led UCLA in scoring with 16 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
