<HEADLINE>
<P>
BETTING WITH BOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Times handicapper Bob Mieszerski lost $30 Sunday when Earth Angel, the first 
horse in his parlay from Earth Angel to Patchy Groundfog, ran third in the 
fourth race. The loss left Mieszerski with a $1,187.30 profit for the meeting. 
He started with a mythical bankroll of $1,000. 
</P>
<P>
Each racing day Bob will make at least one bet. He could make a straight win 
bet, he could make a daily double bet, he could make an exacta bet, he could 
make other exotic bets, or any combination of bets. But, he will make at least 
one bet. 
</P>
<P>
Beginning Bankroll $1,000 
</P>
<P>
Sunday's Loss $30 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll $1,187.30 
</P>
