<P>
Semiconductor Slump Seen: Slumping electronics sales have pushed the world 
semiconductor industry into a mini-recession that is expected to last through 
March, a leading market research company said. Growth in the worldwide 
semiconductor industry is expected to slow to 11% this year and only 1.5% in 
1990, down from a robust 32% in 1988, Dataquest Inc. of San Jose reported in an 
update to its yearly electronics forecast. 
