gang-ridden areas. . . . "Gang kids are abandoning colors as fast as they can," 
says Greg Bodenhammer, director of Back in Control, a parent training center in 
Orange. . . . Wearing black, he says, "gives you safe passage through an area 
where gangs are a problem. Black says, 'Hey, I'm someone to watch out for.' " 
