<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ORANGE; 
</P>
<P>
RECYCLING CHARGE EXEMPTION GRANTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As of Friday, low-income residents participating in the city's recycling 
program will not have to pay the recycling charge of $2.58 per month. 
</P>
<P>
In a memo to the City Council, Mayor Don E. Smith and Mayor Pro Tem Gene Beyer 
recommended the change in response to several seniors asked for the exemption. 
</P>
<P>
Officials said about a third of the city's residents are involved in the 
three-month-old recycling program. Next month, the city will distribute the 
colored bins for recycling to residents in the rest of the city. 
</P>
<P>
Of the total monthly charge, the contractor receives $2.10 for bins, trucks and 
personnel. The city uses the remaining 48 cents for administering the program 
and for various public education programs, such as a children's coloring book 
and poster contests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
