</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Defending NCAA champion Tennessee broke out of a tie with Louisiana Tech to 
capture the top spot in the first regular season Associated Press women's 
basketball poll. 
</P>
<P>
The Vols, which opened Sunday with a 112-39 win over Stetson at Knoxville, 
received 41 first-place votes and 1,527 points from a nationwide panel of 62 
women's coaches in balloting announced today. 
</P>
<P>
Opening with wins over Prairie View and host Oklahoma State at a tournament in 
the Midwest, Louisiana Tech was close behind Tennessee with 21 first-place 
votes and 1,503 points. 
</P>
<P>
Stanford (2-0) remained in third after taking the Communiplex tournament in 
Cincinnati this weekend with wins over Michigan State and Ohio U. The Cardinals 
totaled 1,420 points and got the remaining first-place vote. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach State (2-0), with impressive wins over Eastern Washington and 
then-No. 17 Maryland, jumped two positions from ninth to seventh. 
