<HEADLINE>
<P>
6 RACES CANCELED DUE TO ICY TRACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CANANDAIGUA, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dangerous track conditions forced officials to cancel the last six of eight 
races Sunday at Finger Lakes Race Track. 
</P>
<P>
Track officials said jockeys found the track conditions too dangerous to race 
after the first two races had been run. 
</P>
<P>
An overnight rain storm left water standing on the track surface, under which 
the ground had frozen during a recent cold snap, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Tuesday is the last day of racing for Finger Lakes' 54-day fall meet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
